The product description doesn't really tell you much about the uses for tapioca maltodextrin. Chances are if you're at this page, you must have heard about it from molecular gastronomy related sources.<br /><br />This powder is able to absorb liquid fats and turn them into powders. So far I have been able to make chocolate powder, olive oil powder and bacon oil powder with it. I think in smaller quantities it can also be used in milkshakes to give it some body and bulk.<br /><br />The 1lb tub is quite huge, unless you're working with it on commercial scales it is plenty for the home cook. khymos.org has a whole bunch of recipes you can try with this compound.<br /><br />While you're at it, get some xanthan gum too!
